creator: Maia Technology Pty Ltd
descriptionHtml:
The MaiaGrazing Mobile App is designed for in-field use with the MaiaGrazing web app.
 
The App works with an existing MaiaGrazing account, and requires a valid username/password for a registered MaiaGrazing user. For more information, see http://maiatechnology.com.au/
 
MaiaGrazing is an online grazing management system providing advanced decision support for graziers. It analyses pasture, animal and rainfall information to help farmers make informed decisions in the paddock, managing production risk while increasing grazing performance and profitability. It enables the farmer to dynamically and optimally match their stocking rate to their true carrying capacity, making best use of feed on offer to exploit trading opportunities.
 
This app provides a subset of the functionality available through the full online system. With this mobile app, you can:
 
· View the list of paddocks and see which mobs are in which paddocks.
· View the list of mobs and drill down to stock details within a mob.
· Review upcoming mob moves based on your grazing plan, make adjustments or create an ad-hoc move.
· Enter detailed paddock/pasture observations, stock observations, and comments while moving a mob.
· View and enter rainfall entries for your property.
· Work offline - you can view and enter data even when there is no network connection. The app will synchronise with the online system when a network connection is available, and let you work offline when it isn't.
 
The mobile app is intended to enable simple and quick in-field data capture. The full web version uses this data for detailed paddock and stock analytics, feed budgeting, stock flow (gross margin) reporting, grazing charts and grazing plans.
descriptionShort: The MaiaGrazing App is designed for in-field use with the MaiaGrazing web app.

appDetails.recentChangesHtml: Displaying graze information for multiple mobs/herds in the same paddock. Plus minor bug fixes.
